</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4132E9366B9DD2C7FC0D2781" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574132E9366B9DD2C7FAEA26A1" blockId="26.[151,1436,151,1871]" box="[199,1341,1198,1223]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366B9DD2C7FE9326A1" bold="true" box="[199,324,1199,1223]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<collectingRegion id="38082FB54132E9366B9DD2C7FF2826A1" box="[199,255,1199,1223]" country="Afghanistan" name="Khost" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Host</collectingRegion>
plant
</emphasis>
. 
<superScript id="0DB94C1F4132E9366A08D2C6FE8C26D0" attach="right" box="[338,347,1198,1206]" fontSize="6" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ο</superScript>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366A01D2D8FD9626A1" authority="Mayr." authorityName="Mayr." box="[347,577,1199,1223]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366A01D2D8FE2F26A1" box="[347,504,1199,1223]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Pinus sibirica</emphasis>
Mayr.
</taxonomicName>
(“ 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366907D2C7FD4A26A1" authority="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer, 2013" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[605,669,1199,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366907D2C7FD4A26A1" box="[605,669,1199,1223]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Xyela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D38B803E4132E93669FED2C7FD3726A0" box="[676,736,1199,1222]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E93669BDD2C7FBE826A1" authority="Gussakovskij" authorityName="Gussakovskij" box="[743,1087,1199,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamtschatica">
cf. 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366851D2C7FC4826A1" box="[779,927,1199,1223]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">kamtschatica</emphasis>
Gussakovskij
</taxonomicName>
” of 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366F34D2C7FAE626A1" author="Verzhutskij, B. N." box="[1134,1329,1199,1223]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref72566" refString="Verzhutskij, B. N. (1981) Rastitel'noyadnye nasekomye v ekosistemakh vostochnoy sibiri. Nauka, Novosibirsk, 303 pp." type="book" year="1981">Verzhutskij 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574132E9366B9DD2BAFADD271C" blockId="26.[151,1436,151,1871]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366B9DD2BAFEC8268D" bold="true" box="[199,287,1234,1259]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Biology</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366A74D2BAFDD7268C" author="Verzhutskij, B. N." box="[302,512,1234,1258]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref72566" refString="Verzhutskij, B. N. (1981) Rastitel'noyadnye nasekomye v ekosistemakh vostochnoy sibiri. Nauka, Novosibirsk, 303 pp." type="book" year="1981">Verzhutskij (1981)</bibRefCitation>
reported the imagines to be rather common in the Baikal region. They are active from May to June. One male we studied was collected in the beginning of April. The larvae can be found from June to July. Some of the studied imagines are densely covered with ca 25 µm large pollen grains. Pollen analysis showed that these large tricolpate grains pertain to a non-coniferous plant species (
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366F0BD357FA8C2731" author="Faegri, K. &amp; Iversen, J." box="[1105,1371,1343,1367]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref68103" refString="Faegri, K. &amp; Iversen, J. (1993) Bestimmungsschlussel fur die nordwesteuropaische Pollenflora. G. Fischer, Jena, Stuttgart and New York, 85 pp." type="book" year="1993">Faegri &amp; Iversen 1993</bibRefCitation>
). The Mongolian females were collected in the clearing of a wood with conifers and birches (
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366F3DD30AFB29271C" author="Kaszab, Z." box="[1127,1278,1378,1402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref68821" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1968) Ergebnisse der zoologschen Forschungen von Dr. Z. Kaszab in der Mongolei. 152. Liste der Fundorte der V. Expedition. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, n. s. 21 (1), 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="1968">Kaszab 1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574132E9366B9DD3EEFC0D2781" blockId="26.[151,1436,151,1871]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366B9DD3EEFE3127F9" bold="true" box="[199,486,1414,1439]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74132E9366AAED3EFFDB327F9" box="[500,612,1415,1439]" name="Mongolia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74132E9366934D3EFFD6E27F9" box="[622,697,1415,1439]" name="Russia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Russia</collectingCountry>
(Irkutskaya Oblast) (
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24132E93668FCD3EFFC3D27F9" box="[934,1002,1415,1439]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="20.[151,250,938,961]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,190,902]" captionTargetId="figure-469@20.[151,1436,189,916]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 9. Records of the East Asian Xyela species supposedly feeding on Pinus (Strobus) species: X. kamtshatica (21 specimens from 4 collection sites), X. pumilae (4 specimens from 2 collection sites) and X. sibiricae (8 specimens from 2 collection sites). Additional record of X. kamtshatica by Takeuchi (1938) included for Hokkaido. The rhomb-shaped symbol represents records of X. koraiensis, X. rasnitsyni and X. ussuriensis supposedly feeding on Pinus koraiensis (illustrated separately in Figs 10, 22). Legend for natural distribution of Pinus species: P. koraiensis (solid line, according to Mirov 1967), P. pumila (dotted line) and P.sibirica (dashed line, both combined from Sokolov et al. 1977 and Kremenetski et al. 1998)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261340/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Besides the material we studied from Bolshaya Glubokaya, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366AD5D3C2FD8827A4" author="Verzhutskij, B. N." box="[399,607,1450,1474]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref72566" refString="Verzhutskij, B. N. (1981) Rastitel'noyadnye nasekomye v ekosistemakh vostochnoy sibiri. Nauka, Novosibirsk, 303 pp." type="book" year="1981">Verzhutskij (1981)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned additional records of “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366884D3C3FBC927A5" authority="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer, 2013" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[990,1054,1451,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366884D3C3FBC927A5" box="[990,1054,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Xyela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D38B803E4132E9366F7FD3C3FB4327A4" box="[1061,1172,1451,1474]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366FC1D3C2FA8527A5" box="[1179,1362,1450,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamtschatica">
cf. 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366FE4D3C3FA8527A5" box="[1214,1362,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">kamtschatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from Chunoyar (Krasnoyarskiy Kray) and from Bolshiye Koty (Baikal Region).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4132E9366B9DD39BFB1B2529" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574132E9366B9DD39BFEE72434" blockId="26.[151,1436,151,1871]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366B9DD39BFEE3246D" bold="true" box="[199,308,1523,1547]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks</emphasis>
. Compared with the length of the fore wing, 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366806D39BFBDE246D" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[860,1033,1523,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricae">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366806D39BFBDE246D" box="[860,1033,1523,1547]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Xyela sibiricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the longest ovipositor among representatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366AC8D07FFE232449" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[402,500,1559,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366AC8D07FFE232449" box="[402,500,1559,1583]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The relative length of the proximal lobe of the valviceps is shorter than in other species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574132E9366B9DD037FB1B2529" blockId="26.[151,1436,151,1871]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
The sexes have been associated with the help of material Verzhutskij collected in Glubokaya. According to their labeling, all but 
<specimenCount id="ECCA2ADE4132E9366AD0D0EBFDF324FC" box="[394,548,1666,1690]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of this series were collected on 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E93668CBD0EBFBF824FD" box="[913,1071,1667,1691]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E93668CBD0EBFBF824FD" box="[913,1071,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Pinus sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366F31D0EAFAFD24FC" author="Verzhutskij, B. N." box="[1131,1322,1666,1690]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref72566" refString="Verzhutskij, B. N. (1981) Rastitel'noyadnye nasekomye v ekosistemakh vostochnoy sibiri. Nauka, Novosibirsk, 303 pp." type="book" year="1981">Verzhutskij 1981</bibRefCitation>
under the provisional naming “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366ACAD0CFFE0724D9" authority="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer, 2013" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[400,464,1703,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366ACAD0CFFE0724D9" box="[400,464,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Xyela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D38B803E4132E9366A86D0CFFDC824D8" box="[476,543,1703,1726]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366976D0CFFC4324D9" authority="Gussakovskij" authorityName="Gussakovskij" box="[556,916,1703,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamtschatica">
cf. 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E936690CD0CFFD3D24D9" box="[598,746,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">kamtschatica</emphasis>
Gussakovskij
</taxonomicName>
”), which presumably is the host plant. The Mongolian record also fits the distribution range of 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E93669BDD0A3FBD02485" box="[743,1031,1739,1763]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E93669BDD0A3FC8A2485" box="[743,861,1739,1763]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sibirica">P. sibirica</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366833D0A3FBD02485" box="[873,1031,1739,1763]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sibirica">Pinus sibirica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has been ranked as a subspecies of the European 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366A6DD098FE7F2561" box="[311,424,1775,1799]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cembra">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366A6DD098FE7F2561" box="[311,424,1775,1799]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. cembra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366A8DD087FDAE2561" author="Kindel, K. - H." box="[471,633,1775,1799]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref68972" refString="Kindel, K. - H. (1995) Kiefern in Europa. Bildtafeln und Beschreibungen der in europaischen Waldern, Garten und Parks anzutreffenden einheimischen und fremdlandischen Arten. G. Fischer, Stuttgart, Jena and New York, 204 pp." type="book" year="1995">Kindel (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, but it usually is now accredited species status (Richardson 1998). Its range covers a vast area of northern Asia and extends through 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74132E9366805D17AFC7D254C" box="[863,938,1810,1834]" name="Russia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Russia</collectingCountry>
west to 50° crossing the Ural Mountains to Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366BACD15FFEA82529" author="Mirov, N. T." box="[246,383,1847,1871]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref69989" refString="Mirov, N. T. (1967) The genus Pinus. The Ronald Press Company, New York, 602 pp." type="book" year="1967">Mirov 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64132E9366AD1D15FFD9A2529" author="Willis, J. K. &amp; Bennett, K. D. &amp; Birks, H. J. B." box="[395,589,1847,1871]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="107 - 121" refId="ref72882" refString="Willis, J. K., Bennett, K. D. &amp; Birks, H. J. B. (1998) The late Quarternary dynamics of pines in Europe. In: Richardson, D. M. (ed.) Ecology and Biogeography of Pinus. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York, Melbourne and Madrid, pp. 107 - 121 [paperback edition, 2000]." type="journal article" year="1998">Willis et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
), where an occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44132E9366835D150FC272529" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[879,1008,1847,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricae">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454132E9366835D150FC272529" box="[879,1008,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">X. sibiricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be expected.
</paragraph>
